<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1579" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1579">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 319.112D29/2.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Conduct of police<note n="1" xml:id="d1579fn1">See under “Assault upon
                                American citizens in Panama,” under date of July 9.</note> from
                            statements so far received is so outrageous that I recommend request for
                            suspension of Quijano, chief of police, and Ossa, inspector general, who
                            apparently were not present during firing but who are responsible for
                            present dangerous character of police.</p>
                        <p>The supervisory committee thinks it necessary for fair elections, in view
                            of continued efforts of the authorities to intimidate voters, to request
                            Government to order immediate [deposit] of all arms of police in police
                            stations under guard of supervisors during election.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>